# A {{l|en|word}} {{gloss|separable, discrete linguistic unit}}
#*: {{quote-book|enm|year=a.1400|author={{w|Geoffrey Chaucer}}|title={{w|Troilus and Criseyde}}|chapter=Book II|line= 22-28|passage=  »úe knowe ek that in fourme of ≈øpeche is chaunge / With-inne a thousand »ùeer, and '''wordes''' tho / That hadden pris now wonder nyce and ≈øtraunge / Us thenketh hem, and »ùet thei ≈øpake hem so / And ≈øpedde as wel in loue as men now do|translation=You also know that the form of language is in flux; / within a thousand years, '''words''' / that had currency; really weird and bizarre / they seem to us now, but they still spoke them / and accomplished as much in love as men do now.}}
# A [[statement]]; a linguistic unit said or [[written]] by someone:
## A [[speech]]; a formal [[statement]].
## A [[byword]] or maxim; a short expression of truth.
## A [[promise]]; an [[oath]] or [[guarantee]].
## A [[motto]]; a [[expression]] associated with a person or people.
## A piece of [[news]] {{gloss|often warning or recommending}}
## An [[order]] or [[directive]]; something necessary.
## A [[religious]] precept, [[stricture]], or belief.
# [[discourse|Discourse]]; the [[exchange]] of statements.
# The act of [[speaking]] {{gloss|especially as opposed to action}}
# The [[basic]], non-figurative reading of something.
# The way one [[speaks]] {{gloss|especially with modifying adjective}}
# {{lb|en|theology}} The [[Logos]] {{gloss|Jesus Christ}}
#* {{RQ:Wycliffe NT Lichfield|book=John|chapter=1|verse=1|leaf=44|side=r|column=2|passage=IN √æe bigynnyng was √æe '''woÍùõd''' .¬∑ ‚Åä √æe '''woÍùõd''' was at god / ‚Åä god was √æe '''woÍùõd'''|translation=In the beginning was the '''Word''', and the '''Word''' was with God, and God was the '''Word'''.}}
