==Scots==

===Etymology 1===
From ''A'', an unstressed form of {{inh|sco|enm|I}}, itself a reduced form of {{inh|sco|enm|ik}}, {{m|enm|ic}}, from {{inh|sco|ang|ic||I|pos=pronoun}}, from {{inh|sco|gem-pro|*ek||I|pos=pronoun}}, from {{lang|ine-pro|*√©«µh‚ÇÇ}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|stressed}} {{IPA|sco|/…ëÀê/|/aÀê/}},
** {{a|Dundee}} {{IPA|sco|/…õÀê/}}
* {{a|unstressed}} {{IPA|sco|/…ô/}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|sco|pronoun|first person singular||objective|me|possessive|ma|possessive pronoun|mines|reflexive|masel|emphatic|I}}

# [[I]]
#: {{syn|sco|ik|I}}

====See also====
See [[Template:Scots personal pronouns]] for further pronouns.

===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|sco|/…ëÀê/|/…îÀê/}}
* {{a|Northern|Insular}} {{IPA|sco|/aÀê/}}

