{{also|Crow}}
==English==
[[Image:Corvus brachyrhynchos 2.jpg|thumb|A bird; a crow: ''American crow'']]

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/k…π…ô ä/}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|kr≈ç}}, {{IPA|en|/k…πo ä/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-crow.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|…ô ä}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|crowe|sc=Latn}}, from {{inh|en|ang|crƒÅwe}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*krƒÅw≈ç}} (compare {{cog|fy|krie}}, {{cog|nl|kraai}}, {{cog|de|Kr√§he}}), from {{m|gem-pro|*krƒÅhanƒÖ}} ‚Äòto crow‚Äô. See below.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[bird]], usually black, of the genus ''[[Corvus]]'', having a strong conical beak, with projecting bristles; it has a harsh, croaking call.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1922|author=E.R. Eddison|title=The Worm Ouroborus|passage=Gaslark in his splendour on the golden stairs saying adieu to those three captains and their matchless armament foredoomed to dogs and '''crows''' on Salapanta Hills.}}
# The cry of the [[rooster]].
#: {{syn|en|cock-a-doodle-doo}}
# Any of various dark-coloured [[nymphalid]] butterflies of the genus {{taxlink|Euploea|genus|ver=190708}}.
# A bar of iron with a beak, crook, or claw; a bar of iron used as a lever; a [[crowbar]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1796|author=Matthew Lewis|title=The Monk|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=1985|page=267|passage=He approached the humble tomb in which Antonia reposed. He had provided himself with an iron '''crow''' and a pick-axe: but this precaution was unnecessary.}}
#: {{syn|en|crowbar}}
# {{lb|en|historical}} A [[gangplank]] ([[corvus#Latin|corvus]]) used by the Ancient Roman navy to board enemy ships.
# {{lb|en|among butchers}} The [[mesentery]] of an [[animal]].
# {{lb|en|ethnic slur|offensive|slang}} A black person.
# {{lb|en|military|slang}} The emblem of an [[eagle]], a sign of military rank.
#* '''2002''', Ed Goodrich, ''Riggers that Dive'' (page 46)
#*: A young petty officer that must have just received his ‚Äú'''crow'''‚Äù (a single chevron, with an eagle over it) was showing off to several seamen.
#* '''2003''', Jonathan T. Malay, ''Seraphim Sky'' (page 106)
#*: The young man had been threatened with loss of his third class rank, his ‚Äú'''crow''',‚Äù the eagle in a petty officer's sleeve insignia.

