===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|month}}, {{m|enm|moneth}}, from {{inh|en|ang|m≈çna√æ|t=month}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*mƒìn≈ç√æs|t=month}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*m·∏óh‚ÇÅnÃ•s|t=moon, month}}, probably from {{der|en|ine-pro|*meh‚ÇÅ-|t=to measure}}, referring to the moon's phases as the measure of time, equivalent to {{af|en|moon|-th}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|moneth|t=month}}; {{cog|frr|muunt|t=month}}; {{cog|stq|Mound|t=month}}, {{cog|nl|maand|t=month}}; {{cog|nds-de|Maand}}, {{m|nds-de|Monat|t=month}}; {{cog|de|Monat|t=month}}; {{cog|da|-}} and {{cog|nb|m√•ned|t=month}}; {{cog|nn|-}} and {{cog|sv|m√•nad|t=month}}; {{cog|is|m√°nu√∞i|t=month}}; {{cog|la|mƒìnsis|t=month}}; {{cog|grc|ŒºŒÆŒΩ}}; {{cog|hy|’°’¥’´’Ω}}; {{cog|sga|m√≠}}; {{cog|cu|–º—£—Å—ß—Ü—å}}. See also {{l|en|moon}}.

