==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|en|daie|daye}} {{qualifier|obsolete}}

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*d ∞eg ∑ ∞-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|day}}, from {{inh|en|ang|d√¶ƒ°||day}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*dag}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*dagaz||day}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro||*d ∞og ∑ ∞-o-s}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*d ∞eg ∑ ∞-||to burn}}.

Cognate with {{cog|stq|Dai||day}}, {{cog|fy|dei||day}}, {{cog|nl|dag||day}}, {{cog|nds-de|Dag||day}}, {{cog|gsw|D√§i|t=day}}, {{cog|de|Tag||day}}, {{cog|sv|-}}, {{cog|no|-}} and {{cog|da|dag||day}}, {{cog|is|dagur||day}}. Cognate also with {{cog|sq|djeg||to burn}}, {{cog|lt|degti||to burn}}, {{cog|xto|ts√§k-}}, {{cog|ru|–∂–µ—á—å||to burn}} from *degti, {{m|ru|–¥—ë–≥–æ—Ç—å||tar, pitch}}, {{cog|sa|‡§¶‡§æ‡§π|tr=dƒÅh√°||heat}}, {{m|sa|‡§¶‡§π‡§§‡§ø|tr=d√°hati||to burn}}, {{cog|la|fove≈ç||to warm, keep warm, incubate}}.

{{ncog|la|diƒìs}} is a [[false cognate]]; it derives from {{ncog|ine-pro|*dyew-||to shine}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|dƒÅ}}, {{IPA|en|/de…™/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-day.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|en|En-uk-a day.ogg|Audio (UK female)}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-Day.wav|Audio (UK male)}}
