===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*d ∞eg ∑ ∞-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|Monday}}, {{m|enm|Monenday}}, from {{inh|en|ang|m≈çnand√¶ƒ°||day of the moon}}, from {{m|ang|m≈çna||moon}} + {{m|ang|d√¶ƒ°||day}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*mƒÅnini dag}}, a translation ({{m|la|interpretƒÅti≈ç germƒÅnica}}) of {{der|en|la|diƒìs L≈´nae}}. Compare {{cog|stq|Moundai||Monday}}, {{cog|fy|moandei}}, {{cog|nds-de|Maandag}}, {{m|nds-de|Moondag}}, {{m|nds-de|Maondag}}, {{cog|nl|maandag}}, {{cog|de|Montag}}, {{cog|pdc|Mundaag}}, {{cog|da|mandag}}, {{cog|nb|mandag}}, {{cog|nn|m√•ndag}}, {{cog|sv|m√•ndag}}, {{cog|fi|maanantai}}.

