===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*d ∞eg ∑ ∞-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|Tewesday}}, from {{inh|en|ang|tƒ´wesd√¶ƒ°||Tuesday}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*Tƒ´was dag||Tuesday|lit=Tiw's Day}}. This was a [[interpretatio germanica|Germanic interpretation]] of {{cog|la|diƒìs Martis}}, itself a translation of {{cog|grc|·ºåœÅŒµœâœÇ ·º°ŒºŒ≠œÅŒ±}} ({{w|interpretatio romana}}). Cognate with {{cog|sco|Tysday||Tuesday}}, {{cog|stq|T√§isdai||Tuesday}}, {{cog|fy|tiisdei||Tuesday}}, dialectal {{cog|de|Ziestag||Tuesday}}, {{cog|da|tirsdag||Tuesday}}, {{cog|sv|tisdag||Tuesday}}. More at {{m|en|Tyr}}, {{m|en|day}}.
