===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*d ∞eg ∑ ∞-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|sunnenday}} from {{inh|en|ang|sunnand√¶ƒ°||day of the sun}}, from {{m|ang|sunne||sun}}, + {{m|ang|d√¶ƒ°||day}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*sunn≈çn dag}}, as a translation ({{m|la|interpretƒÅti≈ç germƒÅnica}}) of {{der|en|la|diƒìs S≈çlis}}; declared the "venerable day of the sun" by Roman Emperor [[w:Constantine|Constantine]] on March 7, 321 {{C.E.}}.

Compare {{cog|stq|Sundai||Sunday}}, {{cog|nds-de|S√ºnndag}}, {{cog|nl|zondag}}, West {{cog|fy|snein}}, {{cog|de|Sonntag}}, {{cog|da|s√∏ndag}}.

