===Etymology===
{{calque|en|fr|faux-ami}}, from the longer phrase {{m|fr||faux amis du traducteur|t=false friends of a translator}}, first used by Maxime K≈ìssler and Jules Derocquigny in 1928 in their book ''{{lang|fr|Les Faux Amis ou les trahisons du vocabulaire anglais}}'' (''False Friends, or the Pitfalls of the English Vocabulary'').<ref>{{cite-book|editors=Mark Aronoff, Janie Rees-Miller|title=The Handbook of Linguistics|publisher=Blackwell Publishers|date=2001|author=Christoph Gutknecht|chapter=Translation|p=698}}</ref>

