===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|houre|houre}}, {{m|enm|hour}}, {{m|enm|oure}}, from {{der|en|xno|houre#Old_French|houre}}, from {{der|en|fro|houre|houre, (h)ore}}, from {{der|en|la|h≈çra||hour}}, from {{der|en|grc|·Ω•œÅŒ±||any time or period, whether of the year, month, or day}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*yeh‚ÇÅ-||year, season}}. Akin to {{cog|ang|ƒ°ƒìar||year}}. {{doublet|en|hora}}.

Displaced native {{cog|enm|stound|stunde, stound|hour, moment, stound}} (from {{cog|ang|stund||hour, time, moment}}), {{cog|enm|itid|»ùetid, tid|hour, time}} from {{cog|ang|*ƒ°etƒ´d}}, compare {{cog|osx|getƒ´d||hour, time}}.

