#: {{syn|en|instant|jiffy|mo|moment|sec|second|tic}}
# A unit of [[angle]] equal to one-sixtieth of a [[degree]].
#: {{ux|en|We need to be sure these maps are accurate to within one '''minute''' of arc.}}
#: {{syn|en|minute of arc}}
# {{lb|en|chiefly in the plural|[[minutes]]}} A (usually formal) written record of a meeting or a part of a meeting.
#: {{ux|en|Let‚Äôs look at the '''minutes''' of last week‚Äôs meeting.}}
#* '''2008''', Pink Dandelion: ''The Quakers: A Very Short Introduction'', p 52:
#*: The Clerk or 'recording Clerk' drafts a '''minute''' and then, or at a later time, reads it to the Meeting. Subsequent contributions are on the wording of the '''minute''' only, until it can be accepted by the Meeting. Once the '''minute''' is accepted, the Meeting moves on to the next item on the agenda.
# A unit of purchase on a [[telephone]] or other [[network]], especially a [[cell phone]] network, roughly equivalent in [[gross]] form to sixty seconds' use of the network.
#: {{ux|en|If you buy this phone, you‚Äôll get 100 free '''minutes'''.}}
# A point in time; a moment.
#* {{quote-book|en|1675|{{w|John Dryden}}|{{w|Aureng-zebe}}|passage=Tell her, that I some Certainty may bring; / I go this '''minute''' to attend the king.}}
# A [[nautical]] or a [[geographic]] [[mile]].
# An old [[coin]], a [[half]] [[farthing]].
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A very small part of anything, or anything very small; a jot; a whit.
#* {{quote-book|en|1660|Jeremy Taylor|Ductor Dubitantium, or, The Rule of Conscience in all her Generall Measures Serving as a Great Instrument for the Determination of Cases of Conscience|https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A63844.0001.001/1:9.1.4.2|volume=1|chapter=Of the Probable or Thinking Conscience.|passage={{...}}according to the Prophecies of him, which were so clear and descended to '''minutes''' and circumstances of his passion}}
# {{lb|en|architecture}} A fixed part of a [[module]].
# {{lb|en|slang|US|Canada|dialectal}} A [[while]] or a long unspecified period of time
#: ''Oh, I ain't heard that song in a '''minute'''!''
#* '''2010''', Kenneth Ring, ''Letters from Palestine'', [https://books.google.com/books?id=sLMRHc1aqSIC&lpg=PA18 page 18]:
#*: ‚ÄúMan, I haven‚Äôt seen you in a '''minute''',‚Äù he says, smiling still. ‚ÄúMaybe like two, three years ago?‚Äù

