===Gismu | Root Word===
{{jbo-gismu|kla|}}

# {{lb|jbo|selbri}} to [[come]], [[go]], [[travel]]; {{sumti|1}} comes/goes to [[destination]] {{sumti|2}} from [[origin]] {{sumti|3}} via [[route]] {{sumti|4}} using means/[[vehicle]] {{sumti|5}} [also travels, journeys, moves, leaves to ... from ...; {{sumti|1}} is a traveller; ({{sumti|4}} as a set includes points at least sufficient to constrain the route relevantly)]
# {{lb|jbo|sumti}} [[goer]], [[traveller]], [[journeyer]], [[comer]]

===Usage notes===
* {{l|jbo|klama}} does not distinguish between [[coming]] and [[going]].
* When translating to English, choose between the two ("coming" or "going") based on the position of the destination relative to the speaker's position.
** If the destination is away from the speaker, choose a form of "go"
** If the destination is near the speaker, choose a form of "come"

