# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The study of the [[historical]] development of languages, particularly as manifested in individual words.
# {{lb|en|countable}} The [[origin]] and [[historical]] development of a word; the [[derivation]].
#* {{quote-journal|1=en|year=2018|author=James Lambert|title=A multitude of ‚Äòlishes‚Äô: The nomenclature of hybridity|journal=English World-Wide|page=13|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/318367113_A_multitude_of_lishes_The_nomenclature_of_hybridity
|text=The '''etymology''' of the term ''Japlish'' is disputed and contentiously so.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} An account of the origin and historical development of a word as presented in a [[dictionary]] or the like.

