===Etymology 2===
{{defdate|1620}} From the verb {{m|en|swap}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
[[File:Swapping apples.svg|thumb| [[w:en:Alice and Bob|Alice]] has a red apple and Bob has a green apple. After a '''swap''', Alice has the green apple and Bob has the red apple.]]

# An [[exchange]] of two comparable things.
#* {{quote-book|en|1819|{{w|Sir Walter Scott}}|{{w|Tales of My Landlord}}|section=The Bride of Lammermoor|passage=I e‚Äôen changed it, as occasion served, with the skippers o‚Äô Dutch luggers and French vessels, for gin and brandy{{...}} a gude '''swap''' too, between what cheereth the soul of man and that which dingeth it clean out of his body}}
# {{lb|en|finance}} A financial [[derivative]] in which two parties agree to exchange one stream of [[cashflow]] against another stream.
# {{lb|en|computing|informal|uncountable}} Space available in a [[swap file]] for use as [[auxiliary]] [[memory]].
#: {{ux|en|How much '''swap''' do you need?}}

=====Synonyms=====
* {{sense|an exchange of things}} {{l|en|barter}}, {{l|en|quid pro quo}}, {{l|en|trade}}

=====Hyponyms=====
* {{sense|financial derivative}} {{l|en|credit default swap}}; {{l|en|total return swap}}

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|en|swapsies}}

=====Related terms=====
* {{l|en|swap line}}
* {{l|en|swap meet}}

