# {{lb|en|obsolete}} Incapable of independent function.
#* '''1899''', [[w:John Jay Chapman|John Jay Chapman]], ''Emerson and Other Essays'', AMS Press (1969) (as [http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/13088 reproduced] in Project Gutenberg)
#*: In fact, God is of not so much importance in Himself, but as the end towards which man tends. That irreverent person who said that Browning uses ‚ÄúGod‚Äù as a pigment made an accurate criticism of his theology. In Browning, God is '''adjective''' to man.
#: {{syn|en|dependent|derivative}}
# {{lb|en|grammar}} [[adjectival|Adjectival]]; pertaining to or functioning as an adjective.
#: {{syn|en|adjectival}}
# {{lb|en|legal}} Applying to methods of enforcement and rules of procedure.
#* {{RQ:Macaulay History of England|chapter=10|passage=The whole English law, substantive and '''adjective'''.}}
#: {{syn|en|procedural}}
