# {{lb|en|uncountable|obsolete}} [[strength|Strength]]; [[power]]; [[might]]; [[force]] {{defdate|9th century}}.
#* {{quote-book|en|author={{w|William Bonde}}|title=Pylgrimage of Perfection|year=1526|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=OEHzMgEACAAJ&dq=Pylgrimage+of+Perfection+1526&hl=de&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwji3NyNp9jcAhXFDZoKHT-zCmcQ6AEIKTAA|passage=By the '''craft''' of nature.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} [[intellectual|Intellectual]] power; [[skill]]; [[art]].
## [[ability|Ability]], [[skilfulness]], especially skill in making [[plan]]s and carrying them into [[execution]]; [[dexterity]] in [[manage|managing]] affairs, [[adroitness]], practical [[cunning]]; [[ingenuity]] in [[construct]]ing, dexterity {{defdate|9th century}}.
##* {{quote-book|en|author={{w|Geoffrey Chaucer}}|title=Parlement of Foules|year=c. 1381|passage=The lyf so short, the '''craft''' so longe to lerne [‚Ä¶]}}
##* {{quote-book|en|author={{w|George Grote}}|title=A history of Greece|year=1846|passage=The Cycl√¥pes were Bront√™s, Sterop√™s, and Arg√™s,‚Äîformidable persons, equally distinguished for strength and for manual '''craft''' [‚Ä¶]}}
##* {{quote-journal
|en
|date=11 June 2016
|author=Phil McNulty
|title=England 1-1 Russia
|work=BBC Sport
|url=http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36450648
|page=
|passage=England should have had enough against a very ordinary Russia to complete the job but Rooney's removal robbed them of his '''craft''' and guidance and now increases the pressure on Thursday's meeting with Wales in Lens.}}
## [[cunning|Cunning]], art, skill, or dexterity applied to [[bad]] purposes; [[artifice]]; [[guile]]; [[subtlety]]; [[shrewdness]] as [[demonstrate]]d by being skilled in [[deception]] {{defdate|13th century}}.
##* '''1611''', {{w|Bible}} (King James), {{w|Gospel of Mark|Mark}} xiv.1:
##*: The chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by '''craft''', and put him to death.
##* {{quote-book|en|author={{w|Thomas Hobbes}}|title=Leviathan, or the Matter, form, and power of a Commonwealth ecclesiastical and civil|year=1651|passage=[‚Ä¶] you have that Crooked Wisdome, which is called '''Craft''' [‚Ä¶]}}
##* {{quote-book|en|author={{w|Jack London}}|title=The Sea-Wolf|year=1904|passage=We have not the strength with which to fight this man; we must dissimulate, and win, if win we can, by '''craft'''.}}
##: {{syn|en|craftiness|cunning|foxiness|guile|slyness|wiliness}}
## {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[occult|Occult]] art, [[magic]] {{defdate|13th century}}.
# {{lb|en|countable|obsolete in the general sense}} A work or [[product]] of art {{defdate|c. 1000}}.
