===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|del}}, {{m|enm|dele}}, from {{inh|en|ang|d«£l|t=part, share, portion}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*dailiz|t=part, deal}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*d ∞ail-||part, watershed}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|dele||part, portion}}, {{cog|fy|diel||part, share}}, {{cog|nl|deel||part, share, portion}}, {{cog|de|Teil||part, portion, section}}, {{cog|da|del||part}}, [[wikipedia:Swedish_language|Swedish]] ''[[del#Swedish|del]]'' ("part, portion, piece") {{cog|is|deila||division, contention}}, {{cog|got|êå≥êå∞êåπêåªêçÉ||portion}}, {{cog|sl|del||part}}. Related to {{cog|ang|dƒÅl||portion}}. More at [[dole]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[division]], a [[portion]], a [[share]], a [[part]], a [[piece]].
#: {{ux|en|We gave three '''deals''' of grain in tribute to the king.}}
# {{lb|en|often followed by ''of''}} An [[indefinite]] [[quantity]] or [[amount]]; a [[lot]] (''now usually qualified by'' {{m|en|great}} ''or'' {{m|en|good}}).
#* {{RQ:Mlry MrtDrthr|20.17|2|XVIII|xvij}}:
#*: And so they alle bare hym vnto the hermytage / and vnarmed hym / and layd hym in his bedde / & euer more his wound bledde pytously / but he stered no lymme of hym / Thenne the knyghte heremyte put a thynge in his nose and a lytel '''dele''' of water in his mouthe / And thenne sir launcelot waked of his swoune / and thenne the heremyte staunched his bledynge
<!--#*:Than the knyght armyte put a thynge in hys nose and a litill '''dele''' of watir in hys mowthe, and than Sir Launcelot waked of hys swowghe.-->
#* {{RQ:Austen Mansfield Park|chapter=II|volume=I|page=35|passage=There is a vast '''deal''' of difference in memories, as well as in every thing else, and therefore you should make allowance for your cousin, and pity her deficiency.}}
#* '''1851''', {{w|Herman Melville}}, ''Moby-Dick'', Ch.32:
#*: There is a '''deal''' of obscurity concerning the identity of the species thus multitudinously baptized.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1928|author=Lawrence R. Bourne
|chapter=3|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL5387037W Well Tackled!]
|passage=&ldquo;They know our boats will stand up to their work,&rdquo; said Willison, &ldquo;and that counts for a good '''deal'''. A low estimate from us doesn't mean scamped work, but just that we want to keep the yard busy over a slack time.&rdquo;}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-07|author=David Simpson
|volume=188|issue=26|page=36|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}
|title=[http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2013/may/18/falling-upwards-richard-holmes-review Fantasy of navigation]
|passage=Like most human activities, ballooning has sponsored heroes and hucksters and a good '''deal''' in between. For every dedicated scientist patiently recording atmospheric pressure and wind speed while shivering at high altitudes, there is a carnival barker with a bevy of pretty girls willing to dangle from a basket or parachute down to earth.}}
