===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive|archaic}} To engage in trade; to carry on [[commerce]].
#*{{RQ:Bacon Of Usury}}
#*:'''merchandising''' , which is the vena porta of wealth in a State : the second , that it makes poor merchants ; for as a farmer cannot husband his grown so well if he sit at a great rent
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To engage in in-store promotion of the sale of goods, as by display and arrangement of goods.
#: {{ux|en|He started his career '''merchandising''' in a small clothing store chain.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|archaic}} To [[engage]] in the trade of.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To engage in in-store promotion of the sale of.
#: {{ux|en|He got hired to '''merchandise''' some new sporting goods lines.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To promote as if for sale.
#: {{ux|en|The record companies don't get as good a return on '''merchandising''' artists under contract.}}

