===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|en|ang|namian}}, derived from the noun.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|ditransitive}} To [[give]] a name to.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1904|authorlink=L. Frank Baum|first=L. Frank|last=Baum|title=The Land of Oz|passage=I will '''name''' the fellow 'Jack Pumpkinhead!'}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1913|authorlink=Joseph C. Lincoln|first=Joseph C.|last=Lincoln|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL5535161W Mr. Pratt's Patients]|chapter=1
|passage=A chap '''named''' Eleazir Kendrick and I had chummed in together the summer afore and built a fish-weir and shanty at Setuckit Point, down Orham way. For a spell we done pretty well.}}
#: {{ux|en|One visitor '''named''' Hou Yugang said he was not too concerned about climate change and Baishui‚Äôs melting.}}
#:: {{audio|en|One visitor named Hou Yugang said he was not too concerned about climate change and Baishui‚Äôs melting.ogg|Audio (US)}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[mention]], [[specify]].
#: {{ux|en|He '''named''' his demands.}}
#: {{ux|en|You '''name''' it!}}
#* {{quote-web|en|title=UN Study: China, US, Japan Lead World AI Development|url=https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/un-study-china-us-japan-lead-world-ai-development/4769094.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207184548/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/un-study-china-us-japan-lead-world-ai-development/4769094.html|archivedate=7 February 2019|work={{w|Voice of America}}|date=3 February 2019|passage=The three countries were '''named''' in a new study from the UN‚Äôs World Intellectual Property Organization, or WIPO. }}
#*:: {{audio|en|The three countries were named in a new study from the UN‚Äôs World Intellectual Property Organization, or WIPO.ogg|Audio (US)}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[identify]] as relevant or important
#: {{ux|en|'''naming''' the problem}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To publicly [[implicate]].
#: {{ux|en|The painter was '''named''' as an accomplice.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To designate for a [[role]].
#: {{ux|en|My neighbor was '''named''' to the steering committee.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|Westminster system politics}} To initiate a process to temporarily remove a member of parliament who is breaking the rules of conduct.
#* {{quote-text|en|date=2013-07-10|authorlink=John Bercow|first=John (Speaker of the House of Commons)|last=Bercow|others=to MP {{w|Nigel Dodds}}|passage=I must warn the Right Honourable gentleman, that if he persists in his refusal to comply with my order to withdraw [the words "deliberately deceptive"], I shall be compelled to '''name''' him.}}

