==Latvian==
{{wikipedia|lang=lv}}

===Etymology===
Proposed in 1908 as part of the new Latvian spelling by the scientific commission headed by [[w:KƒÅrlis Mƒ´lenbahs|K. Mƒ´lenbahs]], which was accepted and began to be taught in schools in 1909. Prior to that, Latvian had been written in German [[Fraktur]], and sporadically in [[Cyrillic]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{lv-IPA|f}}
{{audio|lv|lv-riga-f.ogg}}

===Letter===
[[File:Latin alphabet Ff.svg|thumb|200px|F]]
{{lv-letter|upper=F|lower=f}}

# {{Latn-def|lv|letter|9|ef}}

====Usage notes====
The letter '''''F'''''/'''''f''''' (like '''''H'''''/'''''h''''', and '''''O'''''/'''''o''''' representing [o], [oÀê] instead of [u…ôÃØ]) is found only in words of foreign origin (borrowings).

