==Italian==
{{wikipedia|a (prefisso)|lang=it}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|it|la|ad|ad-}}.

====Prefix====
{{head|it|prefix}}

# {{l|en|ad-}} {{q|indicating direction}}

====Usage notes====
The Italian prefix ''a-'' often reduplicates the following consonant ([[:w:en:Syntactic gemination|syntactic gemination]], ''[[w:it:Raddoppiamento fonosintattico|raddoppiamento fonosintattico]]'').
The actual forms usually will be {{m|it|ab-}} (in {{m|it|abbracciare}}), {{m|it|ac-}} (in {{m|it|accorrere}}), {{m|it|ad-}} (in {{m|it|addestrare}}), {{m|it|al-}} (in {{m|it|allargare}}) etc.

===Etymology 2===
Borrowed from {{bor|it|grc|·ºÄ-}}.

