* {{l|es|en-}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{der|es|grc|·ºÄ-}} ({{m|grc|·ºÄŒΩ-}} immediately preceding a vowel; generalized from the many Latin borrowings using this prefix.

====Prefix====
{{head|es|prefix}}

# [[#English|a-]], [[non-]], [[-less]]

=====Usage notes=====
* Used with stems that begin with consonants except ''h''. {{m|es|an-}} is synonymous and is used in front of words that start with vowels and ''h''. For example, {{m|en|analfabetismo||analphabetism}}.

===Derived terms===
{{prefixsee|es}}

===Further reading===
* {{R:DRAE}}

