==Latin==

===Etymology===
From the Latin preposition {{m|la|ab||from, away from, of}}.

===Prefix===
{{head|la|prefix}}

# [[from]], [[away]], away from
# [[off]]
# at a [[distance]]
# [[completely]], [[thoroughly]]
# [[absence]] of
# more [[remote]]
# removed by three [[generation]]s
#: {{m|la|abamita|'''ab'''amita|great-great-grandaunt}}
#: {{m|la|abavia|'''ab'''avia|great-great-grandmother}}
#: {{m|la|abavunculus|'''ab'''avunculus|great-great-granduncle}}
#: {{m|la|abavus|'''ab'''avus|great-great-grandfather}}
#: {{m|la|abmƒÅtertera|'''ab'''mƒÅtertera|great-great-grandaunt}}
#: {{m|la|abnep≈çs|'''ab'''nep≈çs|great-great-grandson}}
#: {{m|la|abneptis|'''ab'''neptis|great-great-granddaughter}}
#: {{m|la|absocer|'''ab'''socer|great-great-grandfather-in-law}}

====Usage notes====
* Before ''b'', ''m'', ''sp'' and ''v'', the prefix becomes {{m|la|ƒÅ-}}.
* Before ''c'' and ''t'', the prefix becomes {{m|la|abs-}}.
* Before ''f'', the prefix becomes {{m|la|au-}}.
* Before ''p'', the prefix becomes {{m|la|as-}} (but with some exceptions).

